ively impaired bankwest operated under its own banking license until  and the cba had planned to operate bankwest under its own cba license and extend to bankwest its basel ii advanced accreditation by  october refer the cba  and  profit announcements and results presentations had the cba kept the bankwest commercial loan book it the cba would have faced a  billion increase in recurring interest costs and regulatory and capital holding costscalculation estimate from the outset the cba made no attempt to capital raise the extra  billion in tier  capital share capital in the case of bankwest instead the cba only raised  billion in payment of bankwests existing share capital the initial purchase price in avoidance of raising the extra  billion in bankwest tier  capital bankwest under reported the bankwest commercial loan book by  billion in its first basel ii risk disclosure dated  march  the cba then proceeded to unconscionably write off  loans having face facility values of  billion in bankwest pre acquisition commercial loans an average loan value of  million per loanrefer the cba answers to questions on notice to the pjc the bankwest  december  financial statements and the share sale deed the bankwest risk disclosures and the cba  and  results presentations the  april  dispute notice in a recentwhen nsw supreme court case the cba admitted that this alleged conduct should it be proven in court is fraudulent and is the worst conduct imaginable levelled at an australian banking license holdercitation needed at the  december  pjc inquiry hearing attorney general phillip ruddock offered for the cba to accept the appointment of independent agreed mediators to determine the facts and circumstances relating to the impairment of the bankwest commercial loan book as opposed to the establishment of a forthcoming royal commission the cba refused an information memorandum contemplating a  billion class action against the cba on behalf of the bankwest commercial loan book victim