e cba chairman john turner admitted that the cba at the time the cba bought bankwest it was not able to replace the bankwest wholesale funds he stated if you think back to  when all this occurred and you think about the executive of the bank the top of the bank they were deeply concerned that the bank continued to existit was the time when wholesale funds for banks were almost impossible to obtain it was the time when the commonwealth bank bought bankwest because bankwest was in an awful lot of trouble and the board had auditors in to every meeting to ensure just to ensure that we came through this financial crisis satisfactorily right through to  — john turner commonwealth bank chairman  the cba strategyedit ian narev the current ceo was the group head of strategy with responsibility for corporate strategy development mergers and acquisitions and major cross business strategic initiatives he led the group’s  billion acquisition of bankwest in  and developed the strategy outlined below the share sale deed provisions provided the cba at clauses    with price adjustment provisions the warranty clauses are     schedule  cl  and clause  c of the share sale deed provided the cba with a  billion short term loan in support of the warranty clauses refer the share sale deed and the december  cba testimony to the pjc the warranty provisions of the share sale deed enabled the cba to deduct amounts from the hbos  million loan it had secured refer above for pre acquisition bankwest loans it the cba deemed retrospectively impaired bankwest operated under its own banking license until  and the cba had planned to operate bankwest under its own cba license and extend to bankwest its basel ii advanced accreditation by  october refer the cba  and  profit announcements and results presentations had the cba kept the bankwest commercial loan book it the cba would have faced a  billion increase in recurring interest costs and regulatory and capital holding costscalculation estimate from t